Also, look for appearances by legendary country & western stars Marty Robbins and Faron Young.

Other stars include George 'Gabby' Hayes, Chief Thundercloud, and the lovely Pauline Moore (Young Mr. Lincoln, Charlie Chan at Treasure Island)

programme.title: Little Annie Rooney (1925)
programme.desc: Mary Pickford, the queen of the silent screen, stars as a tough young ragamuffin who protects her neighborhood from a dangerous street gang. You may wonder why a 33-year-old woman is playing a girl, but this is little Mary, as people liked her best – ready to fight at the drop of a hat! Noted film historian Kevin Brownlow hailed this movie as "remarkable... All the artistry, technical skill, and emotional impact of a medium only thirty years old shine triumphantly through." Can Mary save the day? You bet!

Starring William Watson, Julie Ange, and Ron Charles.

When his corpse is inadvertently brought back to life during a scientific experiment, he makes good on his deadly promises! This oddball feature was directed by Jack Pollexfen, a former newspaperman turned screenwriter, whose credits include Daughter of Dr. Jekyll, and The Man From Planet X...

His plan is to learn about the criminal mind, and what better way than to...well, you know. Obviously, this isn’t the Love Boat! Victor Halperin (White Zombie) directed this tale based on a story by none other than Jack London. Sit back and enjoy. Just don’t let the man with the scalpel near your head!

programme.title: Attack of the Giant Leeches (1959)
programme.desc: Massive bloodsucking monsters are at large in this Drive-in schlock classic from producers Roger and Gene Corman. The legendary Yvette Vickers (Attack of the 50-foot Woman) stars along with Jan Shepard, Ken Clark, and some nasty giant leeches! Basically, they're just a bunch of actors in plastic costumes, but director Bernard Kowalski (Hot Car Girl, Night of the Blood Beast) made the most of his small budget. When the Cormans wouldn't hire a crew to push the camera raft while filming water scenes in the Pasadena Arboretum, Kowalski put on a bathing suit and did it himself!

programme.title: Home in Oklahoma (1946)
programme.desc: The entire gang is here! Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Gabby Hayes, and Trigger are all involved in a murder mystery involving the death of a wealthy ranch owner. Songs include ‘I Wish I Was A Kid Again’ and ‘Cowboy Ham and Eggs’.

programme.title: Cheers for Miss Bishop (1941)
programme.desc: Original TFD Introduction by Dana Hersey. Adapted from Bess Streeter Aldrich's novel Miss Bishop, Cheers for Miss Bishop is a sweeping, tragic epic of lost love and missed opportunities spanning the course of nearly fifty years in the life of the eponymous Ella Bishop. In a spellbinding performance, Martha Scott (Ben Hur, Our Town) portrays Bishop, a teacher at a small Midwestern college who has endured an inordinate amount of misfortune, including broken engagements, ill-fated extramarital affairs and the untimely deaths of many of her close friends. (BW)

programme.title: Border Phantom (1937)
programme.desc: Barbara Hartwell is about to be arrested for the murder of her uncle. It's up to Larry O'Day and his sidekick Lucky to find the real killer and clear Barbara of the charges. Directed by S. Roy Luby for Republic Pictures, Border Phantom is a potboiler from the heyday of Hollywood's Poverty Row. Bob Steele plays Larry, and his brain must be spinning in this one, especially when he finds himself trying to solve a mystery involving wealthy Chinese bachelors and "picture girls" being smuggled across the Mexican border.

programme.title: Julius Caesar
programme.desc: The growing ambition of Julius Caesar is a source of major concern to his close friend Brutus. Cassius persuades him to participate in his plot to assassinate Caesar but they have both sorely underestimated Mark Antony.

programme.title: Our Daily Bread (1934)
programme.desc: John and Mary were at Hell's crossroads, beaten down by the Great Depression. Rather than stay in the city, they flee to the country where they start a farming commune. Overcoming the local authorities, and weather that makes farming impossible, they not only survive, but thrive! Directed by the great King Vidor (The Crowd, Duel in the Sun), the film stars Karen Morley and Tom Keen, and features cinematography by four time Oscar nominee Robert H. Planck (Little Women, Anchors Aweigh). It's an uplifting tale of what people will go through, all for their daily bread.

programme.title: Rhythm in the Clouds (1937)
programme.desc: A struggling songwriter crashes at the home of a famous composer in this sophisticated comedy from Republic Pictures. When she pretends to be his collaborator and writes a hit song, the screwball merriment begins! Starring Patricia Ellis (Block-Heads, Picture Snatcher), Warren Hull (Mandrake the Magician, Night Key), William Newell, and many more! Songs include ‘Two Hearts Are Dancing’ and ‘Mad Symphony’.

programme.title: Marie Galante (1934)
programme.desc: Spencer Tracy stars in this stirring drama about an abducted woman (Katti Gallian) who finds herself involved in a plot to destroy the Panama Canal. This movie has an impressive pedigree: Two-time Oscar nominee Henry King (Twelve O’clock High, The Snows of Kilimanjaro) directs; the cinematography is by seven time nominee John F. Seitz (Sunset Boulevard, The Lost Weekend), and the music is by five time nominee Arthur Lange (The Great Zigfield, The Woman in the Window).

programme.title: The Rebel Set
programme.desc: THE BIG JOLT from BEATSVILLE! Directed by Gene Fowler Jr., "The Rebel Set" (1959) follows the story of three beatniks, hired to rob an armored car on a trip between Los Angeles and New York. Before they can carry out the job, double-crossing and murder get in their way. Starring Gregg Palmer, Kathleen Crowley, Edward Platt, John Lupton, and Don Sullivan.

programme.title: Strange Love of Martha Ivers (1946)
programme.desc: When Sam Masterson (Van Heflin) returns to the neighborhood of his youth, he finds that his old friend Martha (Barbara Stanwyck) has married local District Attorney Walter O'Neil (Kirk Douglas, making his screen debut). All seems fine on the surface, but Walter, Martha, and Sam share a horrible secret. Soon Sam finds himself drawn into Martha's web of fear and suspicion, and the results are classic film noir! Directed by Lewis Milestone ("All Quiet on the Western Front") the film also features the iconic noir goddess, Lizabeth Scott!

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 30

programme.desc: Vincent Price stars in this thriller about a down­trodden country estate that becomes the site of a horrific murder. Prolific writer/director Crane Wilbur (He Walked by Night, Crime Wave) helms this feature, with a cast that includes Agnes Moorehead, Gavin Gordon, and in her last film role, Darla Hood of the Our Gang comedies. But which of them is the mysterious killer known as “The Bat”? You’ll find out soon enough. But beware – the scream you hear may be your own!

programme.title: Beast from the Haunted Cave
programme.desc: A giant spider stalks a band of thieves in this schlocky thriller from Gene Corman Productions. The story follows gangster Alexander Ward and his crew as they enlist the help of a local ski-instructor in the heist of several gold bars. But when they use explosives to create a distraction, they disturb the lair of a massive spider! Monte Hellman, the man behind such cult favorites as Two-Lane Blacktop, made his directorial debut with Beast From Haunted Cave. Trivia note: This movie debuted on a double bill with The Wasp Woman.

programme.title: Bluebeard (1945)
programme.desc: It’s the tale of the infamous serial killer of Paris, Bluebeard! Cult director Edgar G. Ulmer is behind this film that follows the story of puppeteer and portrait artist, Gaston Morrell (John Carradine). Also starring Jean Parker and Nils Asther, this Poverty Row drama is still loaded with macabre thrills!

programme.title: The Big Gap
programme.desc: A man swindled out of $1,500 life savings from a familiar bunco scam, substitute jewelry for cash, jewelry is imitation.

programme.desc: A holdup man is sticking up bars. After he takes the money he kills many of his victims. Sargeant Friday has few leads other than that the holdup man likes a certain song on the jukebox and likes to drink scotch and water.

programme.desc: Laverne Cox: I'm From Mobile/New Teacher Encounters Homophobia In Second Week/Coming Out Again To Grandma With Alzheimer's/Gender Bending And Runway Walking In A McDonald's Parking Lot/Homeless, Transgender And Finding Her Way/Trans Woman Sacrifices Everything To Finally Be Herself/Transgender High School Student Encounters Cyberbullying/A Broken Down Car, Matching Tattoos, And A Love Story/Agender Person Goes From Being Bullied In The Newark Projects To Gracing The Cover of French Vogue/ Alan Cumming: True Bisexual Stories S1 E1-10 | Laverne Cox remembers the bullying she experienced as a child, and how it's similar to the transphobia she experiences as an adult. Megan received a special phone call from her grandma, though, that she'll remember forever. After being kicked out of her home at 17, Angela Louis struggled with homelessness, abusive relationships, sex work, and depression, all while transitioning, but nothing could stop her from finding her own path and earning her diploma. Mila Jam had it all, or so she thought. Her drag persona, Britney Houston, had a massive YouTube following and she performed on a hit TV show in London. But she gave it all up so that she could finally live her truth as a woman and as herself. Olivia Page was brave enough to transition in high school. Unfortunately, a classmate decided to cyberbully her on Facebook. Olivia also had the support and kindness of a teacher who helped her through high school. A wild series of events led Sam to meeting the love of her life. Andre J. wants to tell you one thing: Love Yourself. That's how Andre went from being bullied in the projects to appearing on the cover of French Vogue. Alan Cumming remembers when he first felt an attraction to guys and how he came out to American media in a big way. - Externals

programme.title: TransMilitary
programme.desc: The 2018 SXSW Audience Award-winning feature film debut by Gabriel Silverman, Fiona Dawson, & Jamie Coughlin, TransMilitary follows the Emmy-nominated short film Transgender, at War and in Love. Around 15,500 transgender people serve in the U.S. military (notably the largest transgender employer in the U.S.), where they must conceal their gender identity because military policies ban their service. TransMilitary chronicles the lives of four individuals (Senior Airman Logan Ireland, Corporal Laila Villanueva, Captain Jennifer Peace & First Lieutenant El Cook) defending their country’s freedom while fighting for their own. They put their careers and their families’ livelihoods on the line by coming out as transgender to top brass officials in the Pentagon in hopes of attaining the equal right to serve. The ban was lifted in 2016, but with President Trump now trying to reinstate it, their futures hang in the balance once again.

programme.title: Femme
programme.desc: From executive producer Rachel Brosnahan (The Marvelous Mrs. Maisel), comes a hilarious and moving story of self-acceptance. After being rejected for being too Femme, Carson learns to embrace his truth by way of a drag queen fairy godmother.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E1-2 | Lucy is a “very good ally” who stares at her best friend Miranda…. a lot. They hatch a plan to start Gay Prom Royalty together to promote equality at their school. Miranda pays Lucy a visit on a day off from school. We get a glimpse into Lucy’s home life.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E3-4 | Lucy visits the Gay Straight Alliance to gain support for Gay Prom Royalty. She shares some personal secrets to old and new friends. Anita’s throwing a party and a surprise promposal! Lucy has social anxiety about it.

programme.title: Baby Steps
programme.desc: From Oscar-winning Producer Li-Kong Hsu (Ang Lee’s The Wedding Banquet, Crouching Tiger Hidden Dragon, Eat Drink Man Woman) and Stephen Israel (Swimming With Sharks and G.B.F.), comes this multi-cultural comedy-drama, which takes a funny but honest look at gay family issues in complicated dynamo of a cross-generational Taiwanese and American family. Danny, a Taiwanese-American man, longs to have a baby with his American partner Tate, but their attempts at international surrogacy are complicated by Danny’s meddling mother, who wants to control every aspect of the process -- all the way from Taipei.

programme.title: Single Record

programme.title: Amplify Voices
programme.desc: S1 E6 | We are beginning to realize that it is not enough to be an ally. It’s time now to educate ourselves and prepare to address and attack racism, transphobia, and homophobia head on.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Savannah is a ray of light in the LGBTQ+ youth community and she wants to be a Disney animator one day. She is a member of the Mormon church and has been all of her life however when Savannah came out to her to ward during a sacrament meeting a year ago, the Bishop had her microphone turned off, stopping her right before she had wrapped up her speech. She has since become an advocate for LGBTQ+ teens.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Cody (Elton Cray) is a professional musician & rapper. We did an initial interview with him in his home, then visited with him almost 10 months later at one of his shows. An interesting and passionate man who speaks his mind, Cody's music is about his struggles with himself and others around him who have been indifferent to how he identifies.

programme.title: America In Transition
programme.desc: S1 E1 | After growing up misunderstood in India, Nina fell in love with another trans woman in the United States. Facing the threat of deportation, Nina and her love continue to fight for space to live and flourish when no place feels safe.

programme.title: Scrum

programme.title: Rave Train

programme.title: Engaged
programme.desc: ENGAGED is a short romantic comedy that follows Darren (Daniel K. Isaac), who keeps trying – and failing – to propose to his boyfriend Elliot (Ryan Jamaal Swain). When their relationship is put into an uncomfortable spotlight during a friend’s outrageous engagement party, Darren realizes he actually might be self–sabotaging himself due to unresolved insecurities about his sexuality.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: The Q Agenda

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S1 E6 | Actor Erik Liberman joins The Q Agenda to discuss the importance of onscreen LGBTQ representation, and promote his book on the iconic actress Jayne Mansfield. Actor Darryl Stephens from Noah’s Ark, the first LGBTQ show with a majority black cast, shares his experiences on the show and the state of LGBTQ media representation.

programme.title: Amplify Voices
programme.desc: S1 E6 | We are beginning to realize that it is not enough to be an ally. It’s time now to educate ourselves and prepare to address and attack racism, transphobia, and homophobia head on.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Savannah is a ray of light in the LGBTQ+ youth community and she wants to be a Disney animator one day. She is a member of the Mormon church and has been all of her life however when Savannah came out to her to ward during a sacrament meeting a year ago, the Bishop had her microphone turned off, stopping her right before she had wrapped up her speech. She has since become an advocate for LGBTQ+ teens.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Cody (Elton Cray) is a professional musician & rapper. We did an initial interview with him in his home, then visited with him almost 10 months later at one of his shows. An interesting and passionate man who speaks his mind, Cody's music is about his struggles with himself and others around him who have been indifferent to how he identifies.

programme.title: America In Transition
programme.desc: S1 E1 | After growing up misunderstood in India, Nina fell in love with another trans woman in the United States. Facing the threat of deportation, Nina and her love continue to fight for space to live and flourish when no place feels safe.

programme.title: Scrum
programme.desc: The lives of a self-assured Canadian jock, a rookie Irish backpacker and a stoic Japanese outsider change when they vie for a position in the grueling Bingham Cup.

programme.title: Rave Train
programme.desc: Rave Train is a video series that features live EDM DJ and Artist performances with a diverse range of dancers from the Rave culture. SOUL TRAIN meets EDM; Rave Train brings movement to sound with the latest dance styles with today’s upcoming Electronic Music artists.

programme.title: Engaged
programme.desc: ENGAGED is a short romantic comedy that follows Darren (Daniel K. Isaac), who keeps trying – and failing – to propose to his boyfriend Elliot (Ryan Jamaal Swain). When their relationship is put into an uncomfortable spotlight during a friend’s outrageous engagement party, Darren realizes he actually might be self–sabotaging himself due to unresolved insecurities about his sexuality.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S1 E5 | Enrique, Juliana and Lianna discuss bisexuality. Anthony Ramos joins The Q Agenda to talk about the goals of GLAAD and how they work with celebrities to make sure their Q agenda gets passed. Filmmaker and dreamer Jorge Xolalpa opens up about coming out twice, once for his sexuality and again as a DACA Dreamer.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S1 E6 | Actor Erik Liberman joins The Q Agenda to discuss the importance of onscreen LGBTQ representation, and promote his book on the iconic actress Jayne Mansfield. Actor Darryl Stephens from Noah’s Ark, the first LGBTQ show with a majority black cast, shares his experiences on the show and the state of LGBTQ media representation.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S1 E1-3 | Alice and Veronica attempt to tell band manager Karen that they've broken up - as a band and a couple. They quickly learn that breaking up is not an option. Alice and Veronica start work on their second album. Band manager Karen introduces a new collaborator: the former CB3 child star turned pop starlet Lulu St. Claire. Axis Records executive Richard shows up to hear Alice and Veronica's progress on their new album. Alice takes a step forward with Lulu.

programme.title: Barbelle
programme.desc: S1 E4-6 | Alice and Veronica prepare for a live interview. Veronica is shocked by a discovery. Veronica and Alice shoot a music video with an eccentric French Canadian music video director. Alice and Veronica crash Lulu's ultra lame birthday party replete with pop, chips, and weird uncles. Lulu attempts to keep her budding romance with Alice a secret from her religious parents while Veronica gets up to her usual disruptive antics.

programme.title: No Time For Quiet
programme.desc: Struggling to establish a sense of belonging and identity, a group of teenagers find their voice through a unique rock 'n' roll community.

programme.title: Words
programme.desc: "Words" explores how people navigate gender & identity in the open & evolving landscape of NYC. Featuring exclusive interviews from a variety of artists, activists, icons & innovators. Powerful tribute to the language we use to shape our identities.

programme.title: Scales
programme.desc: S1 E1/2/3 | Meet Remy, Gavin, and David living in Atlanta finding balance in their lives. Remy has been single for quite some time, but an unexpected run in, could potentially change his fate./Remy is going to everyone for advice, including 17-year old Dakota Keller. Meanwhile, problems are brewing at home for Gavin and Sheila and David gets a rude awakening from a stranger./A revolving door can allow you to come in and out. In this case, Remy's house happens to be the revolving door, but someone ends up getting stuck. Remy and Sean must deal with their past. Sheila takes control of a situation and confronts Remy. Kevin’s sister, Gloria arrives with an update on Kevin’s progress.

programme.title: Scales
programme.desc: S1 E4/5/6 | Remy struggles to deal with the aftermath of his actions. Gavin and Sheila’s relationship continues to suffer. Meanwhile, David and Caleb find common ground with each other./Kevin returns home and Gloria expresses her doubts. Meanwhile, Dakota has news to share. David’s sister, Jade gives him encouragement to move forward. David reaches out to Caleb. Remy must face his past, for once and for all./In the season finale it’s a night of big reveals as the trio head to Caleb’s game night event. Ron has a question for Remy. It’s a game of all truths and not everyone will come out a winner.

programme.title: I Do
programme.desc: A gay Briton living in New York risks losing his family and residency in the United States. He marries a lesbian friend to remain in the country, but things get complicated when he meets the love of his life.↵

programme.title: Gina Yashere: Laughing To America
programme.desc: Filmed live in San Francisco, CA, UK's premier black female comedian, Gina Yashere, has come to America! Her unique take on being a cultural insider and outsider never fails to raise the roof as she gives us her take on the news gripping the nation.

programme.title: Strut
programme.desc: In each episode of Strut, we watch Eddie and her friends transform through their risky new endeavor in unexpected positive ways. Eddie is a geeky porn editor whose low self-confidence has turned her into a 26-year-old hermit. Her friends, Eva (an unemployed artist), Lucy (an intern), and Chandaleer (a trainwreck/fashion model) vow to save her from her unhealthy solitude. When the friends decide to start a high-end escorting agency to earn more money, they convince skeptical Eddie to help them build their business and lift her self-esteem. Together they successfully navigate the adrenaline-fueled escorting industry with Eddie as their CEO and fellow sex worker.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E6 | Marianne Tshihamba joins me to create a vegan take on one of my favorite side dishes.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E7 | Danny Kaylor-Hawkins joins me to prepare a quiet dinner for our husbands.

programme.title: Amplify Voices
programme.desc: S1 E8 | This prestigious panel of openly gay US Ambassadors / Presidential Administrators explores the current challenges and opportunities facing the LGBTQ+ community in the U.S. and around the globe, including how Trump’s administration has impacted civil rights, equal rights and LGBTQ+ rights here and abroad.

programme.title: Queer Icon
programme.desc: S1 E2 | The queer community, until recently, did not have much when it comes to representation in the media. These five stars have shown, that has been changing over the past couple of decades, and changing with a stark quickness.

programme.title: Love V Kentucky
programme.desc: An intimate account of how two Kentucky attorneys with no background in civil rights navigate their passionate opponents, wrangle their reluctant allies, and convince the U.S. Supreme Court to rewrite our nation’s definition of marriage.

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S2 E2 | On meets with his perfume factory before traveling to Tel Aviv for a photoshoot and clothing line collaboration. Meanwhile, we get to know a bit more about his fiancée and his connection to personal training. On is encouraging Dave to open his own gym and dream big.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S1 E7 | Reality show star Murray Swanby stops by The Q Agenda! He gives us the scoop behind all the drama that goes into his new show Men of West Hollywood. The Q Agenda also hosts the leadership of the Men's Health Foundation to give tips and help bust the myths about HIV prevention, PreP and other issues regarding health in out LGBTQ community.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S1 E8 | She knows how to make an entrance! Jessica Wild of RuPaul’s Drag Race fame details her journey from Puerto Rico and encouraging wider public acceptance of drag. We also have fitness expert Luis Suarez with tips on how to get that hot bod, and continue Vogue Magazine's discussion on why Carrie’s relationship with her gay husband in the hit show Sex and the City wouldn’t fly today.

programme.title: 1 Million Happy Nows
programme.desc: The story of Lainey and Eva’s changing relationship as they struggle to deal with the diagnosis of Lainey’s Early Onset Alzheimer’s.

programme.title: Becoming Queen
programme.desc: There has never been a band like Queen, and there never will again. Take a twenty year ride with the people who knew them best.

programme.title: Your Eyes On Me
programme.desc: Your Eyes on Me is a story about a drag queen named Gloria whose life changes when she meets Kandi, a drag virgin auditioning for her next show. As the bond develops between the two, their relationship takes an unexpected turn. Suddenly the past and the choices Gloria made as a young man become a stark reality.

programme.title: My Pride
programme.desc: S1 E1 | A family of lions is disturbed from discussing legends by an unwelcome visitor. A year later, the injured cub earns her Pride Name, but it's not what she hoped.

programme.title: BIFL
programme.desc: Expectations, different shades of intimacy, & what it really means to love someone.

programme.title: The Influencers
programme.desc: Six social media influencers compete for an exclusive brand deal with the latest millennial juice craze: Jücytox. As cameras capture each influencer IRL, the manicured versions they present to the world online begin to not just crumble, but implode before our eyes.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: Frameline Voices
programme.desc: A collection of LGBTQ youth-centered shorts with something for audiences of all ages, from the awkward animated memories of Were You Gay in Highschool? to the inspirational story of Zachariah George, aka Mr. Navajo.

programme.title: A Very Sordid Wedding
programme.desc: Seventeen years after family matriarch Peggy tripped over G.W.’s wooden legs in Sordid Lives, same-sex marriage equality has barreled into Winters, Texas and not everyone is ready to accept it. An anniversary memorial service is being planned in honor of Peggy at the bar while the Southside Baptist Church plans an "Anti-Equality" rally to protest the abomination of gay marriage and work to defend their religious freedom. The beloved cast of colorful characters are all on a collision course for shenanigans and fireworks on the big night. Along the way a bisexual serial killer shows up, a drag queen country medley is performed and a beauty-salon-versus-the-bigots battle turns getting your hair done into the front lines of the equality battle. Friendships are tested and families are reunited as fear and bigotry are confronted with acceptance and understanding on the way to a surprise wedding with (almost) everyone in attendance.

programme.title: Out On Stage
programme.desc: Out On Stage is THE absolutely hilarious and one-of-a-kind, originally produced comedy hosted by Zach Noe Towers! See OUT Magazine's "1 of the 10 comedians to watch in 2018," the comedian that Sarah Silverman calls, "So, SO, SO Funny" and 17 other top-rated Gay and Lesbian stand-up comedians discuss taboo subjects as only they can!

programme.title: Freeing the Prisoners of the War on Drugs
programme.desc: In 1971, President Richard Nixon called for a “war on drugs”. His rhetoric set in motion decades of policies that unjustly targeted black and brown Americans and spurred cycles of incarceration directly impacting millions of lives and families. Today, at the same time that multi-state cannabis companies celebrate exponential growth and millions in revenue, people are still languishing behind bars for cannabis offenses. As corporate America and mainstream markets turn their eyes to cannabis, advocates worry that the plight of those victimized by an unjust system will be forgotten. What kind of policies do Americans need to see included in proposed federal legalization to start repairing the damage done by the war on drugs? What responsibility do for-profit companies have to supporting efforts to free prisoners of the war on drugs? Does a shift from punitive to restorative justice ensure that we avoid repeating the mistakes of the past?

Today we have Damon Michaels with us to discuss some of the recent news that’s come out for Mydecine including Health Canada’s approval of the expansion of their cultivation facilities here in Canada. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Canadian expansion means that Mydecine has “instant access” and allows them to supply clinical trials says Michaels - - The possibility of editing mushrooms - - Mydecine facility in Canada probably won’t scale to meet a commercial need, says Michaels - - The roadmap for the next 12 months? Proving efficacy and safety – and looking at protocols

programme.title: How the Psychedelic Industry Can Help Mental Health
programme.desc: Last month we had Dr. Mike Hart for an interview with The Dales Report. Dr. Hart is the Host of Heart to Hart Podcast and a medical doctor at the Ready To Go Clinic, offering treatments to patients that involve cannabis and ketamine. We’re thrilled to have Hart back with us again to discuss the different psychedelic compounds and how they can impact mental health, plus how the industry is benefitting from cannabis’ legalization. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - The psychedelic molecule psilocybin affects mental health in part by breaking up your default mode network - - Psychedelics’ perception benefitting from cannabis’ legalization - - Both cannabis and psychedelic compounds have an impact on empathy and improved mental health - - COVID and financial worry is taking a toll

programme.title: MDMA-Assisted Therapy for PTSD
programme.desc: A new report just released this week by Nature Medicine has a lot of players in both medicine and the psychedelics industry talking. MDMA and other psychedelics like psilocybin have been under scrutiny lately as a possible avenue of treatment for not only PTSD but mental health issues generally. Dr. Mike Hart is back to chat again with us about that report on MDMA-Assisted therapy for severe PTSD. Dr. Hart is the Host of Heart to Hart Podcast and a medical doctor at the Ready To Go Clinic in London, Ontario. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - PTSD very difficult to treat - - Hart says that MDMA-Assisted therapy works because the psychedelic reduces ego - - Hart feels legalization within a year unlikely, and other MDMA-assisted therapy studies will improve

programme.title: Mooneyes : Hot Rod Custom Show 2012
programme.desc: After the cars here in, the bikes were next. This year there were nine motorcycles in total so it was decided to bring them in three at a time. The first group featured Born Free 4 Best of Show winner Matt Olsen on his 1947 H-D Knucklehead, Jeff Wright of Church of Choppers with his personal custom built 1978 H-D Shovelhead and Scott Jones of Noise Cycles with Chaka Khan, a 1978 H-D Shovelhead.

programme.title: Mooneyes : Hot Rod Custom Show 2013
programme.desc: There are a lot of custom bike shows around some large some small, seems to be that a lot of people think their bike is "custom" because they chose a custom paint job, custom grips, pegs and bars from the catalogue provided by the manufacturer. Sure there are all levels of custom from very mild to extreme but for me what makes a custom is the heart, hand and imagination , of the owner / builder, it is not necessary to spend a million bucks, all it takes is passion! At the Mooneyes Hot Rod and Custom show held each December in Yokohama the home town of Mooneyes Japan, Shige Suganuma and his crew of dedicated custom lovers put an enormous effort into bringing you the best of Custom Motorcycles and Cars from around the globe for your viewing pleasure. Passion and imagination are on display on a massive scale, with 650 bikes 250 cars on display and each one jaw droppingly fabulous, the only problem is that the show only runs for one day, you will leave exhausted with aching feet and a brain buzzing with sensory overload, Mooneyes is something you have to see before you die!

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.desc: Three athletes, three elements, three friends. All believing in their own path in life. Each crossing the same road full of doubts, while harnessing their efforts and hunger for a sport, for a job, for a fire that, at this moment, ceases to be hidden.

programme.title: Ireland: Part 1
programme.desc: At the right angles, Ireland can be bold and striking. Water’s unmistakable voice permeates around you as the sounds and rhythms of nature awaken your spirit in Galway Bay, as you gaze out upon the Cliffs of Moher, and more.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Bangkok
programme.desc: Bangkok is a city of sensory overload. Visit the majestic Wat Arun, or The Temple of the Dawn, a Buddhist Temple along the Chao Phraya River. In the heart of Bangkok lies the Grand Palace where visitors gaze upon the Emerald Buddha, and shop the Weekend Market for something authentically Thai.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Once the capital of the world, join Laura in Rome. Travel Rome's oldest road, the Appian Way, and behold St. Peter's Basilica, an Italian Renaissance church that will touch your heart and soul, especially when you view Michelangelo's Pieta. That, and myriad other glorious sites, await you in Rome.

programme.title: Edinburgh
programme.desc: Edinburgh Castle stands boldly atop Castle Rock. Visit St. Margaret's Chapel, the oldest building in Edinburgh, and become acquainted with the legend of Greyfriars Bobby. The Royal Mile and the Grassmarket will keep you busy and fed and tour the waters in luxury aboard the HMY Britannia.

programme.title: Greek Islands
programme.desc: Laura believes the Greek Islands are the perfect destination for a family vacation. Take the island of Hydra, for instance. No cars, trucks, nor buses are allowed, and there is virtually no crime. Cruise by the volcanic island of Poros in private mega-yacht O'Pari before arriving on Aegina Island.

programme.title: San Francisco
programme.desc: Stroll down Grant Street with Laura into the heart of America's largest Chinatown. Bike, drive, or walk across the Golden Gate Bridge, the city's most recognizable landmark. Finally, Fisherman's Wharf offers day trips all wrapped into one fun location.

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: Enter 12 miles of enclosing walls, 26 acres of roof, and over 2,000 windows and experience the royal Palace of Versailles. If you are looking for some good ole' fun, then you will enjoy Parc Asterix. Place Vendome is the top spot for high-end merchandise.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: South Africa
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa knows that an adventurous safari is a wonderful way to experience South Africa. Get up-close-and-personal with lions, giraffes, elephants, and dozens of other animals in their natural habitat, thanks to robust preservation laws in place.

programme.title: Edinburgh and the Scottish Highlands
programme.desc: Climb the ramparts of Edinburgh Castle. Tee up at the world's most famous golf course, St. Andrews. Tour Deward's whiskey distillery. Stroll Stirling's historic battlefields of Braveheart fame. And, sail the bonny banks of legendary Loch Lomond.

programme.title: London
programme.desc: Rudy answers London's call with an expert tour of its traditional sights and contemporary, cutting-edge attractions. In London's breathtaking countryside you will find mythic castles, the real Alice in Wonderland's candy store, Jane Austen's house, and the mysterious megaliths of Stonehenge.

programme.title: Uzbekistan
programme.desc: In one of his series' most colorful episodes, Maxa takes viewers along the Silk Road in a country that is an emerging economy in Central Asia, Uzbekistan. Marvel at eye-popping mosques built centuries ago, and Rudy joins a family for the preparation of the national dish of "plov."

programme.title: Cape Town
programme.desc: Cape Town is a nexus of cultures in a setting so stunning it is called “Africa's Riviera." Where else in the world can you wake up in a cosmopolitan city, spend the afternoon with penguins, ride a funicular to the edge of the continent, and watch the sun set from a beach with a glass of wine?

programme.title: Garden Route
programme.desc: The Garden Route takes you along a rugged, gorgeous South African coastline. Surfers brave enormous waves and exotic birds watch visitors climb serpentine paths that rise above the coast amid seaside resort towns. Also, visit South Africa's lush wine country in the village of Franschhoek.

programme.title: Korea
programme.desc: From the bustling city of Seoul with its 10 million residents to the country's quite countryside, South Korea is a traveler’s paradise. With their misty mountain temples and the uber-modern cities, Koreans mix an abiding sense if history and traditions with a zeal to achieve global success.

programme.title: Best of the National Parks
programme.desc: Each year millions from around the world visit America's national parks, lured by images of lands of wonder beyond expression. This exhilarating program reveals the very best locations in America’s national parks to gaze at geysers, spot wildlife, mountain climb, spelunk, and even tie the knot.

programme.title: Germany's Via Julia
programme.desc: Discover the ancient Roman military road Via Julia that made rapid travel from Lutetia (now Paris) to Constantinople (now Istanbul) possible. Meet the people who keep the memories of this ancient route intact, and who do their utmost to keep the sacred traditions of their ancestors alive.

programme.title: The Road of Money: Mexico to the U.S.A.
programme.desc: Upon landing in Mexico centuries ago the Spanish immediately found silver. The Spanish then constructed a road 3,000 km long to transport the silver from the mines, a road full of hopes, but also riddled with pitfalls and danger. Explore this ancient road from Mexico to the southern United States.

programme.title: The Bahamas - The Heart of the Ocean
programme.desc: As the first lands of the New World to be discovered by Europeans, the Bahamas have always attracted sailors and adventurers. Fed by the warm, nutrient-rich currents of the Gulf Stream, their shallow waters offer today's travelers a crystal-clear sea teeming with marine life.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: Mexico - A Desert Between Two Seas
programme.desc: The Baja Peninsula juts out into the Pacific Ocean like an icicle. The dazzling arid peninsula is a succession of sunset-kissed beaches and trickling creeks. Each year, millions of whales come to reproduce in the preserved waters of the peninsula that their whale ancestors knew so well.

programme.title: South Africa - A Rainbow Nation
programme.desc: With its wide-open spaces and pristine coastline, the province of KwaZulu-Natal has become one of South Africa's ecotourism havens. Away from the carefree atmosphere of its beaches, become a privileged witness to KwaZulu-Natal's well-preserved flora, fauna, and wildlife, possibly “The Big Five?”

programme.title: The Mediterranean Dream - Part 2
programme.desc: Your Mediterranean dream continues in Kotor, Montenegro, an exquisite city set upon the Adriatic Sea. Experience the essence of Greece in Mykonos, Athens, and Santorini, and tour the historic city of Istanbul, Turkey, and Egypt is where some of humankinds most incredible creations still stand.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: France's Burgundy and Loire Regions
programme.desc: The Burgundy region boasts top French wines, romantic canals, Romanesque churches, and world-renowned French cuisine. We base in the small town of Beaune and learn about its history of exceptional winemaking. Add a wondrous hot-air balloon ride over the verdant Loire Valley to the itinerary.

programme.title: Berlin
programme.desc: With world-class cultural sites, dynamic new architecture and unstoppable energy, Berlin is a city on the move. We visit the museums - the ancient treasures of the Pergamon and the Egyptian museum, German Expressionism at the Neue Nationalgalerie and the newly designed Jewish Museum.

programme.title: Munich and Bavaria
programme.desc: Munich's lively Marienplatz pulses with outdoor cafes, shoppers, street musicians, and happy tourists. At the famous Hofbrauhaus sample Bavarian beer and kick up your heels with Schuhplattler dancers clad in lederhosen. Next stop is the Residenz, the family palace built by the Wittlesbachs.

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: Undiscovered
programme.desc: In Disneyland, walk in Walt Disney’s footsteps and discover the secret spots he created. Step inside the newly constructed Disneyland Dream Suite – a magical space in the park’s New Orleans Square. Just around the corner is another secret spot that very few people even have access to – Club 33.

programme.title: The Glacier Express and Gornergrat-Bahn
programme.desc: Go sightseeing on the Glacier Express, an extraordinary railway journey high into the Swiss Alps across 291 bridges, through 91 tunnels, and across the Oberalp Pass at the highest point (2,033 meters, or 6,670 feet, above sea level), and, visit the iconic Matterhorn on the Gornergrat-Bahn.

programme.title: Ireland: Part 2
programme.desc: The gentle side of Ireland shines through in five peaceful locations in Doolin and Kilkenny, where the ancient and the modern meld beautifully together. Nature’s music serenades you as you are reminded of the joys of fresh air, wide open spaces, and the majesty of humanity.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: London
programme.desc: London has played a key role in world affairs for centuries, and as you stroll throughout this magnificent city, history comes to life before your eyes. Buckingham Palace, Campden Market, Covent Garden, the Tower of London, and Cliveden House are just the beginning of the places you will visit.

programme.title: Amsterdam
programme.desc: Whether by foot, bike, or boat, Laura hits all the hotspots in Amsterdam, such as the Rijksmuseum and the Hotel De L'Europe. She even takes a day-trip outside the city to explore neighboring Volendam and picturesque Volendam Harbor and drops into the Rembrandt Hoeve Cheesefarm and Clog Factory.

programme.title: Cambodia
programme.desc: Cambodia has recently risen as a must-see travel destination, and top-notch resorts and hotels have developed to accommodate travelers. Join Laura as she treks to the magnificent temples of Angkor Wat, Bayon, and Ta Prohm via one of Asia's most recognizable animals - the elephant.

programme.title: The Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Begin your stay along the Amalfi Coast in stunning Positano. They say Ravello is a town suspended between sea and sky, and it will leave an impression on you as it has on many artists, musicians, and writers. In Salerno, the gardens at Villa Rufolo will seer into your memory.

programme.title: Saigon
programme.desc: Saigon, Vietnam is an incredible place to visit. It has history, and cultural excursions, like cruising the Mekong Delta and visiting a floating marketplace. In Ho Chi Minh City you can shop until you drop, stay in five-star hotels, and enjoy an incredible culinary experience.

programme.title: Auckland
programme.desc: Auckland is New Zealand's largest city. Laura takes an hour's drive south of Auckland to a working sheep farm in the New Zealand countryside. A few miles down the road, Laura spies a familiar sight - Hobbiton, the set from the Lord of the Rings films where Bilbo lived before and after his journey.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Tahiti and Bora Bora
programme.desc: For sheer tropical splendor, the islands of Tahiti and Bora Bora stand alone. Hyper blue lagoons, white-sand beaches, fish of every shape, size, and color, as well as a generous and welcoming people make these islands key destinations for travelers from around the world.

programme.title: Polynesia
programme.desc: Experience Polynesia’s rich sea life, crystal blue waters, and vibrant cultures. Tour the diverse reefs of the coral, sea turtle rehabilitation centers, and the many islands and atolls. Participate in the oyster-cultivation process at the major pearl farm, and tour dramatic Marquesas Islands.

programme.title: Montreal
programme.desc: Two of the most unique cities in the world are just north of New England. Here you will find brie, pate, jewel box-patisseries, and “s’il vous plait” right along with bagels, maple syrup, hockey, delis, and bocce ball. Those who forged Montreal and Quebec City braved much to see them flourish.

programme.title: Nova Scotia & Newfoundland
programme.desc: From the charming fishing towns of Nova Scotia to the vast wilderness of Newfoundland, explore the last great open spaces of Eastern North America. A touch of New England, a dash of Germany, here a British fort, there an Irish brogue, the area was peopled by the descendants of hardy colonists.

programme.title: Food, Drink, & Culture
programme.desc: In Istanbul’s Spice Market, brown-gold paprika is carefully molded into pyramids. Cinnamon, cumin, ginger, and cardamom infuse the air. From haggis in Scotland to soba and tea in Japan, from asada in Argentina to bibimbap in Korea, food and drink help illustrate the culture and people of a location.

programme.title: Asian Cities
programme.desc: From the world’s largest city, Tokyo, to the colorful chaos of Delhi, and from the modern miracle of Seoul to the teeming streets of Bangkok, this is your passport to the high-tech marvels and back-street secrets of four of the world’s most amazing cities Asian Cities.

programme.title: Travel Thru History
programme.desc: In this episode we visit the Kennedy Space Center located on Florida's famous Space Coast. We will speak to NASA engineers about the past, present and future of American space travel, as well as take a look at the attractions K.S.C. has to offer.

programme.title: Yellowstone: America's First National Park
programme.desc: Vast, beautiful, and untamed, Yellowstone's wilderness ignites the imagination like no other national park. Get a ringside seat for the geothermal wonders, geyser gazing, and diversity of wildlife that gave Yellowstone the nickname, "America's Serengeti."

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia
programme.desc: Italy’s Via Cassia once led north from Rome to Florence, finally joining the Via Aurelia at Luna (now Luni). As you meander northward along the ancient route, each unique location you visit, and the interesting people you meet there, speak vividly to the region’s steeped history and culture.

programme.title: Ecuador: The Road of a New World
programme.desc: In 2007, with the election of President Rafael Correa, the people of Ecuador chose a new way of building towards the future based on the Quechua Indian philosophy of “living well” that focuses on living in harmony with ones’ self, with other people, with nature, and with the Earth.

programme.title: The Bahamas - The Heart of the Ocean
programme.desc: As the first lands of the New World to be discovered by Europeans, the Bahamas have always attracted sailors and adventurers. Fed by the warm, nutrient-rich currents of the Gulf Stream, their shallow waters offer today's travelers a crystal-clear sea teeming with marine life.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Chile - Desert Voices
programme.desc: Known as the driest desert on Earth, the Atacama stretches 1,500 miles along the Andes Cordillera and attracts visitors from all over the world. The intense drought this region experiences helps preserve archaeological sites and geologic features dating back to the origins of the Likan Antai people.

programme.title: Sri Lanka - The Emerald Isle
programme.desc: Sri Lanka is principally known for its heavenly beaches, bold-green mountains and forests, its glorious waterfalls, and renowned tea plantations. It has begun to preserve its ecological resources, and respect the environment more and more, so that everyone may enjoy the land's bounty over time.

programme.title: Tropical and Exotic Asia - Part 1
programme.desc: Begin in lively Hong Kong where there is much to explore. Next, visit four cities in Vietnam: Hanoi, Da Nang, Hoi An, and Saigon, each possessing their own unique characteristics and interesting daily experiences. Complete your first of two tours of Asia with a brief glimpse of Angkor Wat, Cambodia.

programme.title: Fireplace, West Town Chicago
programme.desc: Crowns of flame dance alight beside one another, as sparks twist and rise into the night air like bubbles in a champagne glass. ‘Rest’ is a word so often earned, but less often enjoyed. Time to reap the hard work you have sown. Go ahead. Dream awhile. And rest easy.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Naples and the Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Deep in the heart of Naples, Italy is the ideal launching point for exploring Italy's great historic treasures. Marvel at the ancient city of Pompeii, and the eerily captured devastation of Mount Vesuvius. Hop a ferry to the isle of Capri and drive the spectacular Amalfi Coast.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Rudy is in the city where all roads lead - Roma. We begin in ancient Rome - the Forum, Palatine Hill, Colosseum, and the Baths of Caracalla. Then, we explore the modern city of Rome with its ambient life in the streets, cafes, pizzerias and gelaterias.

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: Hoover Dam
programme.desc: Marvel at the site of America's most famous water dam. We will learn about how the Hoover Dam was built, why it is necessary, and take a behind the scenes look at its inner workings.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: Disney Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Explore the process of designing and creating Disney’s Animal Kingdom with incredible behind-the-scenes footage. Discover how Disney incorporates live animals into their attractions and uncover the time taken to create authentic habitats that allow visitors to experience a safari or jungle trek.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Renaissance Europe
programme.desc: Travelers adore Italy, and Italy adores the Renaissance. In this historical half-hour, we follow Western Europe's transitiical sites and museums in favor of a trip--or a day--just for fun.

programme.title: Europe's Getaways
programme.desc: A key attraction of travel on any continent, including Europe, is that 30 minutes outside any city exists a getaway unlike any you will find on the globe. Truly unique locations that resonate with history and significance. Here, we explore a few such places.

programme.title: Ireland's West Coast
programme.desc: Our trip to Ireland's west coast begins in Galway, Europe's fastest growing city, shopping for Irish crystal and Celtic jewelry. Then it is a salt-sprayed trip to the fabled Aran Islands where we reach breathless heights at a Stone Age fort and ferret out traditional hand-knit sweaters.

programme.title: Dublin and Beyond
programme.desc: Irish eyes are smiling when we explore Dublin, Ireland's urban core. There is history around every corner, and Dublin delights with Trinity College, the Book of Kells, the famous Guinness Brewery, and the infamous Kilmainham jail where Irish rebels spent their last days.

programme.title: Germany's Romantic Road
programme.desc: The Romantic Road winds through some of Germany's most picturesque countryside complete with medieval villages and Baroque Palaces. We start our journey in Wurzburg where we visit the spectacular Baroque Bishop's Palace or Residenz and taste wine at one of Wurzburg's many wine festivals.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Thailand, The Andaman Islands
programme.desc: Andaman Coast towns such as Phuket are well known to backpackers and sun seekers. Join Rudy as he paddles through hidden entrances of small islands to find mangroves few people ever see. Also, visit the dramatic limestone cliffs and rock formations jutting out from translucent waters of Phang-nga Bay.

programme.title: Estonia
programme.desc: Venture to Estonia and the islands of Saaremaa and Muhu where you will find windmills, thatch-roofed farmhouses, and quiet waters. Rudy interviews Mart Laar who took over Estonia under tough conditions following the withdrawal of Soviet troops and turned it into a dynamic country.

programme.title: St. Petersburg, Russia
programme.desc: From the splendors of Peterhof to the quiet grace of the city's canals, this former capital built by a czar has reclaimed its position as one of the world's great destinations. St. Petersburg--enjoying a renaissance since its favorite son, Vladimir Putin, ascended to office—has lifted its gloom.

programme.title: Buenos Aires, Argentina
programme.desc: The style and verve of one of South America's most beautiful capitals is highlighted with Argentina's national dance, the tango, as well as the energy that its diverse population brings to the urban landscape. Discover a very special place in Buenos Aires.

programme.title: Mendoza, Argentina
programme.desc: As Rudy ascends into the thin air of the Andes, he stops to visit the graveyard of those who died climbing Aconcagua. Rudy’s next choice for high-altitude adventure? Getting soaked whitewater rafting. Back at sea level he meets winemakers whose elegant Malbecs are shaking up the world's wine market.

programme.title: India: From Girl to Woman
programme.desc: “First marriage and then love.” This Indian proverb describes Indian society quite accurately in terms of how the tradition of marriage is perceived and experienced in the country. In India, people do not just marry whoever they wish. It is the family that decides in an arrangement called Shaadi.

programme.title: Kyoto, Japan
programme.desc: The spiritual heart of Japan, Kyoto offers a glimpse of Japanese life as it used to be, primarily because it was spared during World War II. Comfortable streets with wooden homes, impressive temples, and a dedication to ancient Japanese traditions make Kyoto one of Japan's most visited cities.

programme.title: Yosemite America's Treasure
programme.desc: Experience Yosemite's breathtaking icons like the granite monoliths El Capitan and Half Dome and behold the splendor of Bridal Veil and Yosemite Falls. Explore Yosemite's deep history as the first land set aside for preservation, and a land that inspired John Muir and photographer Ansel Adams.

programme.title: Portugal's Via Publicae
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: From Ouagadougou to Conakry: The Road of Possibility
programme.desc: In Burkina Faso, Mali, and Guinea, explore the “Africa of Possibility.” This is a continent with solutions, thanks to crafty people and their capacity to adapt. The Road of Possibility is more than journey from Ouagadougou to Conakry. On these tricky roads, obstacles trigger unique encounters.

programme.title: Fiji - Island Flavors
programme.desc: The Fijian Archipelago consists of more than 300 islands scattered across the South Pacific Ocean. In Fiji, everyone can find an island that suits them, as you retrace the trail of Robinson Crusoe in this incredible paradise.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Madagascar - A Multifaceted Land
programme.desc: Madagascar split off from Africa some 150 million years ago. The isolation of being separated from the mainland caused the island's wildlife to develop distinct and unique features. Once a pirate stronghold, today Madagascar has opened itself up to the world, and is revealing its secrets.

programme.title: Laos - Along The Mekong
programme.desc: Isolated from geopolitics for the past 30 years, Laos is now slowly opening to tourism. Its cultures and environment are fragile, and a responsible form of tourism could preserve its past and character. From fishing villages to the forests of northern Laos, meet the people that protect their land.

programme.title: Tropical and Exotic Asia - Part 2
programme.desc: The first destination on the second leg of your Asian journey begins in Bangkok, an energetic city replete with temples and markets. Singapore and the Spice Islands are also on the agenda, as is an incredible underwater adventure in Indonesia. Your tour of Asia ends in Bali and a Kecak performance.

programme.title: Fireplace Upstate New York
programme.desc: Few things can soothe the spirit more than a warm, crackling hearth on a cold mountain night. Licks of fire dance in the crisp mountain air as the surrounding stone soaks in the heat of the flames, and suddenly, you feel as if you are inside a cozy cabin with nothing but time to burn.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava

programme.title: Madrid

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam

programme.title: Savannah

Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance

programme.title: Disney Cruise Line

programme.title: Angry Planet | The Unstoppable Force of Bangladesh
programme.desc: Ground zero for climate change and at risk of being wiped off the map, George is in Bangladesh during monsoon season to see how resilient and creative locals are adapting to their increasingly hostile environment.

programme.title: Angry Planet | Vanuatu
programme.desc: Climate change deniers claim volcanoes produce more greenhouse gases than fossil fuels do. George investigates this claim while revisiting the active volcano of Marum in Vanuatu. He dons a fire-suit and descends 1200 feet into the volcano.

programme.title: The 1920s
programme.desc: Mobsters, jazz, and turbulent economic times mark the 1920s. Silent film makes the transition to the talkies as sound comes to the silver screen. Criminals find that there is one less place to hide with the invention of the lie detector, and the Space Age is launched.

programme.title: Shaytana's Eye
programme.desc: The peaceful Kingdom of Kale is thrown into chaos after the Citadel is overthrown by the dark forces of Kreel and Xax. After his family farm is destroyed by the Xaxian army, young William Tell is visited by the mystical Kalem who reveals that he has been chosen to seek the legendary Crystal Arrow.

programme.title: Halloween Party
programme.desc: Ozzie and Thorny take it upon themselves to plan a non-costume party as the only costumed individuals, dressing up as Satan and a Scotsman, respectively. Meanwhile, Ricky and David attend a Halloween Party at school, and the Nelson household is besieged by children demanding candy, or else.

programme.title: Riviera Ballet
programme.desc: Ozzie has two tickets to the Riviera Ballet, but Harriet does not wish to attend the event because the dancers in the ballet will be wearing skimpy attire.

programme.title: Thorny's Gift
programme.desc: Ozzie is insulted after buying Thorny a lighter for his birthday, wrapping it in Christmas paper, mailing it, and not getting a "thank you” for the gift. Tired of listening to Ozzie’s bellyaching, his family forces him to confront Thorny about the matter by locking Ozzie out of the house until he does so.

programme.title: Paradise Lost
programme.desc: Newlyweds Ben and Joanna's happiness is short-lived when Parsons leads a pirate attack on the family. The arrival of a merchant ship rescues the Robinsons. Back in Boston, David stands trial for the murder of Parson's brother.

programme.title: Bank Book 6565696
programme.desc: Rob discovers Laura's secret bank account book and wonders why she is keeping it a secret from him. Rob concludes she must be saving money to buy him a birthday present, such as a new movie projector she knows he wants. When he receives a shirt instead of a projector, the mystery perplexes Rob.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis travels to London, Ontario for Steve Plunkett's Country Cruize-In.

programme.title: Sioux City; Dade County Canal; Lady in Green; Affair of the Heart
programme.desc: A woman is brought back to life after her car sinks at the bottom of a canal. Is a mysterious lady in green to thank for Joe Trucker's miraculous recovery? The patients of an experimental heart surgery meet and fall in love. And many more stories that prove the existence of miracles.

programme.title: Baby Comes to Life: Burning from Within; Tara's Angels; Healed by Kindness; Dannion Brinkley
programme.desc: A baby is born lifeless and declared dead, but after 78 minutes, miraculously comes to life. A Vietnam veteran is struck by lightning while talking on the phone and is dead for the next 28 minutes. After his experience he gained the ability to predict the future and communicate with the dead.

programme.title: Paradise Lost
programme.desc: Newlyweds Ben and Joanna's happiness is short-lived when Parsons leads a pirate attack on the family. The arrival of a merchant ship rescues the Robinsons. Back in Boston, David stands trial for the murder of Parson's brother.

programme.title: Part 4
programme.desc: After Charles Sr. helps discharge Charlie from the School for Orphans, Charlie discovers his innate ability as an actor, and convinces his father to reunite with his mother. Then, when life challenges the Chaplins once again, Syd returns.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis goes for a spin in a Lincoln Cosmo and Model A Rod.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis travels to London, Ontario for Steve Plunkett's Country Cruize-In.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.
