programme.title: Ford Frontier Fishing
programme.desc: There are fishermen in this world; wise fishermen, expert fishermen, wonderfully skilled fishermen, and then there is Lefty Kreh. For over 60 years Lefty has been the fisherman's fisherman - more important though are all the years that Flip Pallot has been able to call him, simply - friend. They take on bass in the back waters of eastern Texas on this episode of Fishing Frontiers.

programme.title: Cedar Lake Skis
programme.desc: Cedar Lake in Perrault Falls, Ontario, Canada, is a diverse musky fishery with multiple water colors and structural elements. Jim Saric and musky hunter Bob Turgeon grind through post-frontal conditions and sift through shallow cover utilizing boatside tactics to trigger Cedar Lake Skis to bite.

programme.title: Burning Up the Bay
programme.desc: The Great Lakes are home to some of the best musky fisheries across North America. In summer, the muskies often establish a home range around large, shallow weed flats. Jim Saric and Pro Guide Bret Alexander encountered a pack of muskies on an overcast and rainy summer day and with the biometrics being high, they burned blades covering water quickly, trigging strikes from multiple muskies.

programme.title: Togiak I
programme.desc: ‘Hunting’ Silvers on the Togiak River

programme.title: The Rut is On
programme.desc: Cameron Hanes stalks a giant bull in New Mexico, while Mark Garcia of Archer Xtreme gets in the middle of rutting bulls in Colorado.

programme.title: Grateful
programme.desc: A young hunter’s first elk hunt ends in a GIANT way, while David Blanton of Realtree gets a crack at his biggest bull ever.

programme.title: Yellow Creek Wyoming
programme.desc: Wind and cold weather are on the docket for hunters in Wyoming with Dallas Safari Club’s Outfitter of the Year B. Joe Coy. Getting into range of these mature whitetails is tough when the stiff wind keeps changing directions on Mr. Whitetail.

programme.title: No Laughing Matter
programme.desc: Larry Weishuhn – the Elvis of deer hunters – heads to Machen Ranch in south Texas to rattle in a mature whitetail buck during the peak of the rut. Senator John McCain joins Larry to discuss the second amendment and the future of deer hunting.

programme.title: Top of the Flyway
programme.desc: It's an annual pilgrimage at the as Chris Dorsey and brother Joe venture to Alberta to catch the beginning of North America's annual waterfowl migration.

programme.title: Before We Sink
programme.desc: The Brigade must contend with a crack in their voyageur canoe in preparation for an epic lake crossing and the most dangerous stretch of rapids. With time a constant pressure and the threat of failure looming, a storm threatens to freeze one of the brigade members. The team receives a surprise from home.

programme.title: Feral Sheep Hunting in Argentina
programme.desc: Jim heads the Argentina to go after some of the cool Barnyard sheep species.

programme.title: Number One Client
programme.desc: Despite his busy schedule, Tom never misses an opportunity to take Jacque on a hunt.

programme.title: Good Times and Good Bulls
programme.desc: Bowhunter's Mike Carney and friends chase bugling bull elk at Cross Mountain Ranch in northwestern Colorado.

programme.title: Texas Bone-Collecting
programme.desc: Stan Potts is headed to south Texas to collect bone at the Partidas Ranch with his buddy Michael Waddell, Dr. Deer shares the advantages of fire in mangement in your management plan, Mr. Shelton talks in-season archery practice and Jeremy Moore delivers part two of a three part series on shed dogs.

programme.title: Super Grouper
programme.desc: Chef Scott Leysath got a ton of grouper from his buddy, Tommy Gomes, and he’s cooking it up 3 different ways. Joining him on the show are Susie Jimenez, Stacy Lyn Harris, Brad Fenson, Cee Dub, and Buddy T.

programme.title: The Reluctant Bottom Feeder
programme.desc: Derek traverses Wisconsin for backbreaking labor on the Mississippi River, and a backbreaking fun at a hog wrestling tournament. Featuring Jeff Ritter.

programme.title: Offshore Gulf Grouper
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Seth Hayes for some incredible offshore gag grouper action off the coast of Ft.Myers.

programme.title: Backwater Series in the Everglades
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Donnie Kish in search of redfish and the first place trophy.

programme.title: Golden Fly Part 2
programme.desc: It’s Day 2 of the Golden Fly Tarpon Tournament in Islamorada, FL. Rob is fishing tournament champion Andy Mill and Bou is fishing his friend Paul Nute.

programme.title: Golden Fly Part 3
programme.desc: It’s Day 3 of the Golden Fly tarpon Tournament in Islamorada, FL. Rob and Andy Mill have had a productive week, but will need a strong finish to win the event.

programme.title: Young Salt, Old Spirit
programme.desc: Armed with the skills of generations past, rough and tumble New Englanders teach the SFTV crew how to catch the region's sporty summertime species.

programme.title: Atlantic Gladiators
programme.desc: New England pelagics like swordfish and bluefin tuna bring more than sport. It's a heavyweight, high octane battle, and the angler is the underdog.

programme.title: Catch Me If You Can
programme.desc: Three days, five release flags, 400 photos: the SFTV crew and Marlin magazine join forces to chase blue marlin and sailfish at Panama's Tropic Star Lodge.

programme.title: Jacks Be Roiling
programme.desc: When word gets out that Jack Crevalle are in a feeding frenzy, Justin and fellow Captain Kyle Pitts speed down the Intracoastal Waterway to find them doing just that.

programme.title: Aftermath Bite
programme.desc: Travis and Justin head out after Hurricane Michael and find it hard to keep fish off the hook

programme.title: Flint Oak Upland
programme.desc: Join Jeff Fuller, along with his sons, Clayton and Callahan, and the dogs of Soggy Acres Retrievers as they travel to Flint Oak Hunting Resort in Kansas for an upland hunt to remember.

programme.title: Missouri Mega Blind
programme.desc: The hunt for ducks starts in southern Missouri in a mega blind that’s the stuff of waterfowl dreams.

programme.title: Get Their Good Tidings
programme.desc: Chris Dorsey returns to the mountains of Colorado to hunt mule deer in the rut.

programme.title: Our Dwellings Shape Us

programme.title: Best of Season 9

programme.title: Canada 1

programme.title: S&W Classics

programme.title: Larry Potterfield's Matched Purdey Shotguns
programme.desc: Host Joe Mantegna visits Larry Potterfield and discusses his beautifully matched pair of James Purdey and Sons 12-gauge shotguns.

programme.title: Drew Benton - Seminole
programme.desc: This season of ZAFS has been a test, every show was hard earned. It should come as no surprise that it would wrap up the same way. Z heads south to Georgia's Lake Seminole to meet up with Bassmaster Drew Benton, who knows these stomping grounds like the back of his hand. Of course they will roll out just ahead of a massive polar vortex. But, like this season, sometimes the greatest tests have the best payoff.

programme.title: Electric Goes Hollywood
programme.desc: Often, changes in the US and in other parts of the world are spearheaded by famous actors, sports players, singers, and politicians. For many years now, high-profile individuals have been supporting the change from gas to electric vehicles. - How do many in Hollywood and beyond feel about electric cars? Dozens of famous people have been spotted in their EVs and Hybrids! Here are some famous celebrities in electric cars.

programme.title: Truck Yeah! - The Electric Trucks Are Coming

programme.title: Flying On Electric
programme.desc: Electric aircrafts could be landing at an airport or rooftop near you within five years. Electric aircraft will offer a smoother, quieter ride, with a smaller carbon footprint, and airfares are expected to be comparable with ground transportation.

programme.title: The Sound of Electric

programme.desc: Chelsea Sexton, Paul Scott, Forth Mobility, and several owners come together to discuss how electric cars have evolved and where we currently are in the state of this developing technology. programme.title: Animation: Dynamic All-Wheel Steering – Maneuvering And Parking
programme.desc: An advance in all-wheel steering, the Dynamic All-wheel Steering that is optional in the Audi A6, A7, and A8, is standard equipment in the S8. It is currently the top technology among Audi’s steering systems and combines dynamic steering on the front axle with rear-axle steering. With that system, Audi is exploring the limits of what is physically possible. The system offers significant benefits, specifically in the threshold range. It combines direct, sporty steering response with masterful driving stability or, in brief: manageability with extremely high precision.

programme.title: Animation: Audi Q4 e-tron – Interior and package
programme.desc: With the Q4 e-tron, Audi is presenting a true all-rounder – it is a confident companion for everyday life and leisure, and is suitable in every way as a household’s main car. At 4,590 millimeters (15.1 ft) long, 1,865 millimeters (6.1 ft) wide, and 1,613 millimeters (5.3 ft) high, the exterior dimensions of the Q4 e-tron place it in the larger compact SUV segment. The architecture of the modular electric drive system (MEB) on which the compact electric SUV from Audi is based enables a completely new division of space. While the front overhang measures just 86 centimeters (33.9 in), the wheelbase measures a generous 2.76 meters (9.1 ft) – even more than in the medium-sized SUV segment. The resulting interior measures 1.83 meters (6.0 ft) in length, which is similar to a large full-size class SUV.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Interior Design and Seating Position
programme.desc: The fully electric gran turismo gives new impetus to the Audi design language: It is a dynamic sculpture that stands on the road as if sculpted from a full volume. The Audi e-tron GT proves: The packaging of an electric car with its large battery and the fascinating design of a gran turismo with a flat silhouette and powerful proportions are no contradiction. This is made possible by a recess in the battery pack. The passengers in the rear can put their feet in what is known as the foot garage, which allows them to sit in a lower position and enjoy generous headroom despite the flat roof line. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Infotainment and Operating Concept
programme.desc: Eleven antennas, all of them are invisibly integrated into the car, connect the e-tron GT with the outside world. programme.title: Audi Annual Press Conference 2020
programme.desc: 2020 was dominated by a global pandemic and great upheaval, which therefore shifted the focus even more strongly to the question of responsible actions. As part of the automotive industry, we are responsible for our employees and customers, for stable economic growth, and for a sustainable business model. Despite – or precisely because of – the current challenges, we are in a position where we can make a big difference. At Audi, we see ambitious climate targets, the paradigm shift toward software, and the impetus created by new competitors as an opportunity to play an active part in shaping the future of mobility. Our Board of Management team, which has been active in a new constellation for about a year, will provide an overview on how Audi handled the unusual year of 2020 and on which future topics we have our sights firmly set.

programme.title: Animation: Dynamic All-Wheel Steering – Maneuvering And Parking
programme.desc: An advance in all-wheel steering, the Dynamic All-wheel Steering that is optional in the Audi A6, A7, and A8, is standard equipment in the S8. It is currently the top technology among Audi’s steering systems and combines dynamic steering on the front axle with rear-axle steering. With that system, Audi is exploring the limits of what is physically possible. The system offers significant benefits, specifically in the threshold range. It combines direct, sporty steering response with masterful driving stability or, in brief: manageability with extremely high precision.

programme.title: Animation: Audi Q4 e-tron – Interior and package
programme.desc: With the Q4 e-tron, Audi is presenting a true all-rounder – it is a confident companion for everyday life and leisure, and is suitable in every way as a household’s main car. At 4,590 millimeters (15.1 ft) long, 1,865 millimeters (6.1 ft) wide, and 1,613 millimeters (5.3 ft) high, the exterior dimensions of the Q4 e-tron place it in the larger compact SUV segment. The architecture of the modular electric drive system (MEB) on which the compact electric SUV from Audi is based enables a completely new division of space. While the front overhang measures just 86 centimeters (33.9 in), the wheelbase measures a generous 2.76 meters (9.1 ft) – even more than in the medium-sized SUV segment. The resulting interior measures 1.83 meters (6.0 ft) in length, which is similar to a large full-size class SUV.

programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Interior Design and Seating Position
programme.desc: The fully electric gran turismo gives new impetus to the Audi design language: It is a dynamic sculpture that stands on the road as if sculpted from a full volume. The Audi e-tron GT proves: The packaging of an electric car with its large battery and the fascinating design of a gran turismo with a flat silhouette and powerful proportions are no contradiction. This is made possible by a recess in the battery pack. programme.title: Animation: Audi RS e-tron GT – Electric Quattro and Recuperation
programme.desc: The e-tron GT quattro and the RS e-tron GT usually drive with electric all-wheel drive, only the “efficiency” mode of the Audi drive select dynamic handling system prioritizing the front-wheel drive. In event of a slippery road surface, high power requirements, or fast cornering, the electric motor for rear-wheel drive is also activated here, and around five times faster than with a mechanical quattro drivetrain. The electric all-wheel drive regulates the drive torque distribution between the axles – continuously, fully variably, and within a few thousandths of a second. The quattro principle of the four-wheel drive that Audi introduced to the market more than 40 years ago presents itself on a new, fascinating technological level. When the driver releases the right-hand pedal, the drive usually switches to sailing, allowing the gran turismo to glide with elegance and efficiency. By contrast, the car recuperates in overrun mode in the “dynamic” mode of Audi drive select. - Audi RS e-tron GT: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.2–19.3 (NEDC), 22.5–20.6 (WLTP); combined CO2 emissions in g/km (g/mi)*: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes in ranges depending on the tires and alloy wheel rims used.

programme.title: Animation: Audi Q4 Sportback e-tron – Electric quattro: Torque Distribution and Cooling
programme.desc: The electric all-wheel drive in the Q4 e-tron top models has an asynchronous motor (ASM) on the front wheels that can rev at up to 14,000 rpm. It is installed coaxially and has combined cooling with coolant and oil. The principal advantages of the ASM are its short-term overload capacity and the minimal drag losses when it is inactive – these are important because the front motor does not contribute to the drive in the majority of driving situations for reasons of efficiency. - Audi Q4 Sportback e-tron: Combined electric power consumption in kWh/100 km (62.1 mi)*: 20.9–16.6 (WLTP); 17.9 – 15.6 (NEDC) Combined CO2 emissions in g/km: 0 - Information on fuel consumption and CO2 emissions as well as efficiency classes.

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 3

programme.desc: China's biggest boxing star, Zou Shiming. In the UFC we step outside of the canvas to learn about colour commentator Joe - Rogan and some fighters who became politicians. Finally, it’s Kosovo’s first Olympic gold medallist and more of that trash talk!

programme.desc: Wladimir Klitschko’s return to the ring and Hollywood’s Idris Elba entering the world of combat sports. In the UFC we look at Tito Ortiz and his love life. Finally, Irish boxer Katie Taylor and one of Hollywood’s biggest - stars, Jackie Chan!

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 10
programme.desc: Floyd Mayweather Jr and his post boxing career and some anti trash talkers in the sport. In wrestling, we look at Japan’s big list of medallists at Rio 2016 and finally, it’s the boxer who went from fighting in the streets to the ring, - Robson Conceicao

programme.title: Fight Stars Episode 11

Witness daring escape, mind-blowing mentalists, incredible illusionists, levitations, transformations, and so much more, all performed live on stage in Hollywood!

programme.title: Arachnicide
programme.desc: After successfully taking down the drug operation, a task force composed of six of the best soldiers from different Special Forces Units is called on for an important mission in Albania. There, they discover that an incubator has accelerated the growth of plants needed for the manufacturing of illegal drugs and narcotics which is protected by a group of colossal spiders.

programme.title: Purgatory - SERIES FINALE!
programme.desc: Ep. #2.8-Sunshine With the ultimate revenge for Alex’s death in sight, the group learns the remaining pieces of the puzzle that has plagued them for far too long at this point. The guilty are exposed, and sacrifices will be made to determine who will escape from Purgatory, and who will be left behind to pay for their sins.

programme.title: The Bay- The Beginning
programme.desc: Episode 7- - Marly gets shocking news. Brian finds himself backed into a corner with few options. Sara turns to Commissioner Martin for help. Pete seeks refuge away from the chaotic Garrett estate. Janice has a heart-to-heart discussion with her best friend Christine Nelson, only to soon discover some horrifying news from Lianna. Elliott has a knock at the door that changes his life forever.

programme.title: Tainted Dreams
programme.desc: Let's Fill The Void- - Angelica finds herself alone with Jordan at a bar who reveals a secret about himself, as Max & Kassandra escort each other to a high profIle industry party. All hell breaks loose when Veronica discovers Greg at Liza's apartment. She goes to a bar for comfort and her drunken tirade carries into the next day when she shows up to work intoxicated and attacks her director Henry as the cast & crew watches.

programme.title: Jack Rio
programme.desc: A famous actor in Los Angeles tries to escape his on-screen persona, the T.V. character that has made him famous, and find himself again, while a string of murders seem to follow in his wake. Is it the work of an obsessed fan? Or something far worse?

programme.title: Laura McKenzie's Traveler
programme.desc: Sydney- Sydney Harbor, a sightseeing cruise followed by a fast jet boat ride that makes some exciting 360 spins under the Harbour bridge. Laura climbs to the top of the Sydney Harbour Bridge - a once-in-a-lifetime experience indeed – before she visits her favorite attraction, the legendary Sydney Opera House. Numerous first-rate attractions, world-class museums, excellent shopping, and a year-round calendar of free outdoor events.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Drag Kids
programme.desc: Drag has always been about breaking down barriers and daring to do the unexpected. Now, a new type of queen is on the scene: she’s fierce, she’s living in a time of unprecedented access to queer culture, and she’s younger than ever before. She’s a drag kid and she’s a long way from the era of the queens who led the Stonewall Riots nearly 50 years ago. Stephan, Jason, Bracken and Nemis have never met, but they’re united by a shared passion for drag. They are about to come together for the first time – to perform Lady Gaga’s ‘Born This Way’ at the world-famous Montreal Pride Festival. As they prepare for the big show, each faces their own unique challenges, as well as challenges they have in common - deep feelings of isolation and the struggle of trying to claim a place of your own on the fringes of a fringe culture. Drag Kids is a beautiful, daring, and touching portrait of four kids chasing freedom and friendship through the art of drag.

programme.title: Beethoven - Daniel Barenboim
programme.desc: Qui l'illustre direttore d'orchestra Daniel Barenboim suona e dirige i cinque concerti di Beethoven con l'Orchestra della Staatskapelle di Berlino in occasione del suo 65° compleanno. Il Concerto n. 5 in MI bemolle maggiore, noto come "L'Imperatore", vede il maestro rivoluzionare la forma con un primo movimento lungo seicento battute. Un'improvvisazione messa per iscritto?

programme.title: Balanchine: Jewels - Mariinsky
programme.desc: Girato al Teatro Mariinsky, questo spettacolo vede la partecipazione di alcuni dei più famosi ballerini del teatro di San Pietroburgo, tra cui Ulyana Lopatkina, Igor Zelensky e Andrian Fadeyev, accanto al direttore d'orchestra Tugan Sokhiev. I Gioielli di George Balanchine sono parte integrante del repertorio della compagnia - uno dei più grandi al mondo, sia per numero che per fama.

programme.title: Daniel Barenboim - W. E. Orchestra
programme.desc: Orchestra di portata molto simbolica, la West-Eastern Divan Orchestra è stata creata grazie allo slancio del direttore israelo-argentino Daniel Barenboim e del critico letterario Edward Saïd. Riunisce tutti i giovani musicisti israeliani e dei paesi arabi vicini - come ad esempio la Siria, la Giordania o i territori palestinesi - con un unico obiettivo: gettare dei ponti fra le comunità attraverso la musica. In diretta dalla Philharmonie di Berlino nel 2006, interpretano l’imponente nona sinfonia di Beethoven.

programme.title: Berliner Philharmoniker - S. Rattle
programme.desc: L'illustre Orchestra Filarmonica di Berlino, la Berliner Philharmoniker, ha fatto dell'Europakonzert una tradizione. Ogni anno i suoi musicisti celebrano la fondazione della loro orchestra in una città europea diversa. Nel 2008 si sono esibiti sotto alla direzione del grande direttore d'orchestra Sir Simon Rattle al Conservatorio Tchaikovsky di Mosca. In programma: Il Concerto per violino n. 1 in SOL minore di Max Bruch, la Sinfonia n. 7 di Beethoven e la Sinfonia di Igor Stravinsky in tre movimenti.

programme.title: Mozart Requiem - Claudio Abbado
programme.desc: Sotto la direzione di Claudio Abbado, la Lucerne Festival Orchestra, accompagnata dal Coro della Radio Bavarese e dal Coro della Radio Svedese, ha eseguito con grazia il Requiem di W. A. Mozart al Festival di Lucerna nell'estate 2012. Le voci solenni di Anna Prohaska (soprano), Sara Mingardo (contralto), Maximilian Schmitt (tenore) e René Pape (basso) esprimono la bellezza e la profondità di questo capolavoro.

programme.title: J.S. Bach: Organ Concerts
programme.desc: Per rendere omaggio a Johann Sebastian Bach che ha servito per 27 anni come "maestro di cappella" nella chiesa di San Tommaso a Lipsia, l'organista Ullrich Böhme dà un concerto sul nuovo organo della chiesa: una replica del modello storico che suonava Bach.

programme.title: Berlin Philharmonic: Mahler S. N°2
programme.desc: Il direttore d'orchestra olandese Bernard Haitink, che oggi vanta una sbalorditiva carriera di 65 anni, ha iniziato in qualità di violinista dell'Orchestra Sinfonica della Radio olandese prima che gli venisse affidata, all'età di 32 anni, la direzione del Concertgebouw Concertgebouw di Amsterdam. Vi rimase per 27 anni. Una consacrazione per questo specialista di Gustav Mahler, di cui dirige qui la seconda sinfonia.

programme.title: Esa-Pekka Salonen - Joyce DiDonato
programme.desc: Dal 1994, il Festival di Verbier è un luogo d'incontro musicale internazionale nella Svizzera francese. Grandi artisti vi si esibiscono ogni anno davanti a un pubblico fedele. Nel 2015, il Festival accoglie il brillante mezzosoprano americano Joyce DiDonato. Eseguirà Summer Nights, Op. 7 di Hector Berlioz, sotto la direzione di Esa-Pekka Solonen, il famoso direttore d'orchestra finlandese. Si tratta di sei melodie francesi su bellissime poesie di Théophile Gautier da La Comédie de la mort.

programme.title: The Nutcracker - Mariinsky
programme.desc: Ed è proprio sul palco del Mariinsky di San Pietroburgo che, nel 1892, è stato creato il capolavoro di Tchaïkovski: lo Schiaccianoci. Sullo stesso palcoscenico, 120 anni dopo, l’orchestra del medesimo teatro, sotto alla bacchetta del maestro Valery Gergiev, accompagnata dal prestigioso balletto del teatro Mariinsky, ne offre una versione che non potrebbe essere più fiabesca.

programme.title: Lang Lang - Debut at Carnegie Hall
programme.desc: Anche se Lang Lang aveva a malapena festeggiato il suo 21° compleanno all'epoca di questo concerto, il suo portfolio vanta già una serie impressionante di apparizioni internazionali di alto profilo. La sua selezione di apertura, le Variazioni "Abegg" di Schumann, figura nel debutto alla Carnegie Hall di Yevgeny Kissin nel 1990, mentre la sonata in DO maggiore di Haydn è apparsa due volte durante il celebre debutto dei cinque concerti di Sviatoslav Richter al Carnegie nel 1960.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: The Magic Flute - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Il Flauto magico è l'opera finale di Mozart. Un racconto meraviglioso, una favola popolare o un racconto che marca il periodo della sua maturità, la storia della regina della notte, il principe Tamino, il vanaglorioso uccellatore Papageno e il suo flauto magico, ha lasciato il segno nei cuori e nelle menti. Accompagnato dalla prestigiosa Berliner Philharmoniker Orchestra sotto alla direzione di Simon Rattle, il direttore Robert Carsen rivisita questo classico con un tocco raffinato attraverso una profonda riflessione sulla vita e sulla morte.
